\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b brachystachys} (Hackel) Markgr.-Dannenb., {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  76}: 325 (1978) ({\i F. varia} subsp.{\i  eu-varia }var.{\i  brachystachys }subvar.{\i  typica} Hackel,{\i  F. varia} subsp. {\i brachystachys} (Hackel) Hegi): Sheaths closed for 1/3 their length; ligule 0·4-0·7(-1·3) mm; ribs prominent, glabrous above. Panicle 2·5-6·5 cm, nodding, the branches smooth. Spikelets 8-10 mm distinctly violet-tinged, with 2-4(-6) florets. Upper glume (2·5-)3·5-5·2 × 1·5-2 mm, ovate-oblong, the lateral veins reaching its length. Lemma long-acuminate; awn (0-)0·3-1·3 mm. Palea densely and shortly setose. 2n = 14. 1600-2050{\i  m; calcicole. Mountains of E. Austria}.
