\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b pallidula} (Hackel) Markgr.-Dannenb.,{\i  op. cit. }326 (1978) ({\i F. varia} subsp.{\i  eu-varia} var. {\i brachystachys} subvar.{\i  pallidula} Hackel,{\i  F. varia} subsp.{\i  brachystachys} (Hackel) Hegi): Sheaths closed for 1/4-1/3 their length; ligule 0·4-1·1 mm; ribs not prominent, long-hairy above. Panicle 2·5-5·5 cm, rigid, the branches hairy. Spikelets (6·6-)7-9·4(-10·9) mm, pale, glaucous, with 3-6 florets. Upper glume 3·6-4·5 × 1·3-2·3 mm, ovate, the lateral veins reaching 2/3-3/4 its length. Lemma shortly acute; awn 0(-0·4) mm. Palea densely and shortly setose. 600-1300{\i  m; calcicole. Mountains of E. Austria}.
