\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 32. F. xanthina} Roemer & Schultes, {\i Syst. Veg.}{\b  2}: 721 (1817). Stems 25-58 cm. Leaves 0·3-0·7 mm wide, soft, smooth, subobtuse, the lowest 1/8-1/3 as long as the uppermost; veins 7; ribs 3-5; sclerenchyma forming a ring; sheaths usually retrorsely scabrid, closed for less than ¼ of their length; ligule 0·4-2 mm. Panicle 4-9·5 cm, lax, slightly nodding, the branches with more or less dense, short hairs. Spikelets 8-14(-15) mm, with 3-4 florets, yellowish-green or variegated. Upper glume 5-6 mm, elliptical, rounded. Lemma 4·6-8·5 × 2-3·4 mm, ovate-lanceolate, shortly acuminate, broadly scarious, unawned or mucronate. Palea shorter than to as long as lemma, shortly setose above. Anthers at least ½ as long as palea.{\i  Calcicole. • Mountains of S.W. Romania and E. Jugoslavia.} Ju Rm.
